``Kingaisha''''
There are the following shrines outside the precincts, and all of them are Shikinai shrines. In "Gogun Shrine Record", the two main shrines and the following four princes are called ``Yutomi Rokusho Shrine''.
* Komori Shrine - Deity enshrined: {{ill|lt=Taian Manso|Q384705|WD=Q384705|lt=Taichōshin Yasumanro|1=Ō no Yasumaro}}, Shikinai Kosha/Kosha Kamimei Shrine
* Ojijin no Mikoto Shrine - Enshrined deity: Oshijin no Mikoto, Shikinai Small Shrine/Ojijin no Mikoto Shrine (Ronsha)
* Himeji no Mikoto Shrine - Enshrined deity: Himeji no Mikoto, Shikinai small shrine/Himeoji no Mikoto Shrine (Ronsha)
* Yanari Shrine - Enshrined deity: Yanari Shrine, Shikinai Small Shrine/Yanari Shrine

=== Festival ===
The grand festival is held on the third Sunday in April and is called Ohrenzo (the festival is called Renzo in Yamato). In the era when {{ill|lt=lunar calendar|Q11511066|WD=Q11511066|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar}} was used, the festival was held around {{ill|lt=vernal equinox|Q1339268|WD=Q1339268|1=Chunfen}}.

